Confronting the &ldquo;scars&rdquo; of the past and encouraging women to speak out together - Sally&rsquo;s story of &ldquo;chasing the light&rdquo;
&ldquo;For domestic violence, it is zero times or thousands of times.&rdquo;
Everyone knows it, but few people can get out of the mire of domestic violence.
In the era featuring information overload, it is hard to believe there are few platforms that speak up for victims of domestic violence. It is worth noting that facing difficulties such as the concerns of families and children, and stereotypes of Chinese women, how victims of domestic violence should face up to their difficulties, work hard to defend their rights and get out of the gloom, as well as what kind of mindset they should have to start a better future.
